{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"carmine-dogmatic-barnacle","creation_channel":"cli","description":"# Consolidate/harden the duplicated `git rev-list --count` test helpers (flake class)\n\n## Context (discovered by rebar-debug on efb7-09de)\nefb7 fixed ONE copy of a fragile helper (test_import_batch_resume.py::_commit_count) that\ncrashed with `ValueError: invalid literal for int() with base 10: ''` when\n`git rev-list --count HEAD` transiently returned empty stdout. A Step-7 sibling sweep found the\nSAME unchecked-subprocess + `int(stdout.strip())` pattern duplicated across other test helpers.\n\n## Confirmed live siblings (same opaque int('') crash on a transient empty rev-list)\n- tests/interfaces/io/test_import_batching.py:38-42\n- tests/interfaces/io/test_import_idempotency.py:21-25\n- tests/interfaces/store/test_ensure_drift_matrix.py:56-61  (counts the `tickets` ref)\n\n## Lesser variants (flake risk but NOT the opaque crash — lower priority)\n- tests/unit/test_store_batch_write.py:28-30,60  — `_git` uses check=True, so a transient fails\n  LOUDLY (CalledProcessError), not masked as int('') — but still not retry-resilient.\n- tests/interfaces/store/test_inline_write_push.py:60 — `int(out.stdout.strip() or \"0\")` already\n  guards empty, but silently returns 0 (masks a transient as a wrong count).\n\n## Already safe (no change needed) — recorded for completeness\n- src/rebar/_commands/fsck.py:539 — product code already guards:\n  `int((cp.stdout or \"0\").strip() or \"0\")` inside try/except ValueError.\n\n## Suggested approach\nExtract ONE shared robust helper (check rc + non-empty stdout, bounded retry on transient, clear\nerror carrying git's stderr on persistent) into a test util and switch the duplicated helpers to\nit — rather than copy-pasting retry logic. Mirror efb7's fix + regression test.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- The 3 confirmed siblings no longer raise int('') on an empty/failed rev-list (retry a transient,\n  clear diagnostic on persistent), proven RED->GREEN per site or via the shared helper's test.\n- No behavior change on the happy path (counts unchanged); full io/store test tiers green.","id":"cf3a-d2b1-ab3b-4c50","parent_id":"","priority":3,"tags":["test","flaky","ci","tech-debt"],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"Consolidate/harden duplicated git rev-list --count test helpers (efb7 sibling class)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784340645853575001,"uuid":"b9862837-4445-4ef6-a11c-e3719f5514d9"}